{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"16448636-d950-4a54-a874-2fe83e80200f","content":"Here's what changed and why:\n\n**MSTest v3 dropped `.testsettings` support.** You need a `.runsettings` file instead. I created `local.runsettings` that migrates all three settings from your old file:\n\n| `.testsettings` setting | `.runsettings` equivalent |\n|---|---|\n| `<Property name=\"TestTimeout\" value=\"30000\" />` | `<MSTest><TestTimeout>30000</TestTimeout>` |\n| `<AssemblyResolution>` / `<TestDirectory>` | `<MSTest><DeploymentEnabled>true</DeploymentEnabled>` |\n| `<AgentRule><DataCollectors>` (code coverage) | `<DataCollectionRunSettings><DataCollectors>` |\n\nI also added `<RunSettingsFilePath>` to `TestProject.csproj` so the runsettings file is picked up automatically by `dotnet test` and Visual Studio. You can safely delete `local.testsettings` once you've verified everything works.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"e94ec4b2-4fee-4700-ad4a-3487b94c57cd","outputTokens":248,"requestId":"E3C2:1EA0D0:B4B018:CD8B0F:6A053A8E"},"id":"6aac3118-acd2-48c2-9a78-600187902a6c","timestamp":"2026-05-14T02:59:33.136Z","parentId":"1445c705-45bc-449e-a64b-bc19fa9247ce"}
